<html>
  <head>
    <title>imdb ratings rss</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="/css/style.css">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width">
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="https://unpkg.com/modern-normalize@0.4.0/modern-normalize.css" />
    <script defer data-domain="imdbrss.bitboxer.de" src="https://plausible.io/js/plausible.js"></script>
  </head>
  <body>
    <p>
      Creates an rss feed for public imdb ratings.
    </p>

    <p>
      You can find the rss feed under 
      <code>
        /rss/#{USER_ID}
      </code>. To find out your imdb user ID, go to your
      ratings page and look at this part of the URL:
      <pre>
http://www.imdb.com/user/ur7019649/ratings
                         ---------
      </pre>
    </p>
    <p>
      Example: <a href="https://imdbrss.bitboxer.de/rss/ur7019649">https://imdbrss.bitboxer.de/rss/ur7019649</a>
    </p>

    <hr />
